The paper focuses on developing a deep learning network for traffic light and sign detection, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) categories. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques such as hierarchical architecture and mini-batch selection, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of security and privacy in autonomous cars, which could potentially fall under the computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) category.
